               <p>JOHN COXON PICKEN. I am in the employ of Messrs. Whitakers, of Ave Maria-lane. On the 11th of July, between ten and eleven o'clock at night, I was at the <placeName id="t18320906-68-crimeloc398">Holborn end of Farringdon-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-68-crimeloc398" type="placeName" value="Holborn end of Farringdon-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-68-crimeloc398" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-68-off396 t18320906-68-crimeloc398"></join>, and perceived a few <rs id="t18320906-68-deflabel399" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-68-defend674 t18320906-68-deflabel399"></join>s playing on the pavement - as I passed them I felt a twitch at my pocket; I turned round, and caught hold of a lad, who said, "It was not me, Sir - it was that boy," pointing to the prisoner - I ran, and caught hold of the prisoner, but could not find my handkerchief - I gave him in charge; I had used it a few minutes before; it was found on him at the watchhouse.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-68-person677">
                  WILLIAM 
                  LEE
               <interp inst="t18320906-68-person677" type="surname" value="LEE"></interp>
